Information control moved in parallel. The president signed an order eliminating the U.S. Agency for Global Media, parent of Voice of America, and placed more than a thousand VOA journalists on administrative leave. Funding for Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty and Radio Free Asia was cut. The White House restricted Associated Press access to the Oval Office and Air Force One after the AP refused to adopt the term \'93Gulf of America.\'94 A judge declined to restore that access, at least for now. On domestic websites, the administration removed a Surgeon General advisory that framed gun violence as a public health issue and took down online applications for student loan repayment plans. The Department of Justice deleted eleven guidance documents on disability rights and Covid-19 under the Americans with Disabilities Act, calling them \'93unnecessary and outdated.\'94\
