The week also saw open intimidation of the judiciary from outside government. MAGA supporters made bomb threats against judges who ruled against the administration, including a Supreme Court justice. The White House\'92s own rhetoric about \'93activist partisan judges\'94 and its attacks on Judge Boasberg\'92s family blurred the line between official criticism and incitement. When the U.S. Attorney General labeled property damage at Tesla facilities as \'93domestic terrorism\'94 and brought heavy federal charges, it signaled that protest-related acts against favored corporations would be treated as threats to national security. At the same time, Steve Bannon dismissed the deportation of innocent people caught up in mass sweeps as a \'93tough break,\'94 making clear that individual rights were expendable in service of a broader campaign.\
